{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Single-Page App Feel\n      Homepage is the entire experience. The 5 nav buttons scroll to sections on the same page (anchor links). Each \"page\" is a full-viewport section: Hero → Statement → 발전계획서 → 실적 → 초심 → About. The nav bar highlights the current section as you scroll.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Extremely simple — one page, one flow\n            Mobile-friendly scrolling experience\n            Easy to maintain — everything in one file\n            Modern, clean feel\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            발전계획서 (15 subsections) could make the page very long\n            About page with full CV may feel cramped as a section\n            Harder to link directly to specific content","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1774738523424}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Minimal Multi-Page (Recommended)\n      Homepage is the hero + nav buttons. Each button leads to its own clean page. 6 total pages: Home, Statement, 발전계획서, 실적, 초심, About. Shared minimal header/footer. Each page is focused and self-contained.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Each page can breathe — 발전계획서 gets its full long-scroll treatment\n            About page works naturally as a full CV\n            Direct URLs for sharing specific pages\n            Homepage stays punchy — hero text + 5 buttons, done\n            Still very simple — just 6 HTML pages with shared layout\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Slightly more files to manage (still only 6)\n            Page transitions instead of smooth scrolling","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1774738540398}
